&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;After welcoming American Economics Advisor to Thailand, Permanent Secretary of Labour M.L. Puntrik Smiti revealed that the United States had consulted and acknowledged policies and structure relevant to anti-child labour and human trafficking. She said that the United States had shown its interest in the Ministry of Labour&#039;s survey to be conducted on child labour and asked that the United States to provide advice in the event the child a labour survey is conducted, as information gained would help the U.S. Department of State remove sugarcane products from the list of good associated with child labour or forced labour. Therefore, consultations with parties considering the information would be extremely beneficial. The consultations with the United States showed great positivity for acceptance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Permanent Secretary of Labour explained the Department of Labour Protection and Welfare&#039;s intentions to invite representatives from the Embassy of the United States and officers to conduct surveys at sugar factories and amongst sugarcane farmers, asking about the current existence of child labour. She said that this would allow a clear picture of current situations and establish a clear understanding. In terms of human trafficking, the United States acknowledged that the Ministry of Labour had compiled a manual on slavery and debt bondage etc., to which the United States showed satisfaction and asked for a copy of the manual to study further in order to provide more advice. In general, the United States showed readiness to support and work together with the Ministry of Labour on resolving the issue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Department of Labour Protection and Welfare assigned Dhurakij Pundit University to conduct the survey which has already been completed. Completed surveys with information from organizations have been sent to the officials at the National Statistics Office for another survey, where it is expected to be ready around the middle of February before the end of the sugarcane harvest period in March 2016.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;The United States understands that different issues have their own complexities, where various countries have the same issues. They are therefore satisfied with what the Thai government, by the Ministry of Labour has done, which will push benefits and rights to international standards,&amp;quot; said the Permanent Secretary of Labour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;In addition to this, emphasis was made that the Thai government and Ministry of Labour has consistently given importance to the prevention and resolution of human trafficking, and has thus issued policies to promote legal employment of foreign workers in order to ensure legally permitted protection and welfare in alignment with international standards. Various measures have been implemented such as the organization of foreign workers, control of recruitment agents, labour inspections, revisions and draft of legislation/relevant regulations, arrangement of workers in the fishing industry, arrangement of Thai workers abroad, elimination of child labour and increased international collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rtecenter&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rtecenter&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;ldquo;OUR HOME OUR COUNTRY STRONGER TOGETHER&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rtecenter&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;ldquo;We will grow stronger together, because this is our home; Thailand is ours.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rteright&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rteright&quot;&gt;Bureau of Public Relations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rteright&quot;&gt;Wichulada Buachai &amp;ndash; News&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;rteright&quot;&gt;Sompob Silbut - Photos&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;8 February 2016&lt;/div&gt;
